identificationRemarks: This specimen appears to be Lampropeltis ruthveni. The range is correct and appearance consistent. A positive ID could be made by counting ventral scales which average about 188. L. ruthveni can be easily confused with L. polyzona. This specimen is not a L. annulata which ranges much further north and east in South Texas, NL, Tamaulipas and Coahuila (primarily in the Tamaulipan Thornscrub).
name: Lampropeltis ruthveni Blanchard, 1920

identificationRemarks: Appears to be this species. Higher band count than L. polyzona. In range for L. ruthveni.
